## USER RESEARCH

### Top 5 Pain Points

1. **"Short nails feel boring"** — Users feel excluded from trending nail content, which skews heavily toward long coffin/almond shapes. They want proof that short nails can be just as editorial and trend-forward.
2. **"I don't know what designs actually work on a small canvas"** — Not all nail art translates to short nails. Users are frustrated by inspo that looks impossible on their length.
3. **"My polish chips within days in summer"** — Heat, swimming, sunscreen, and frequent hand-washing destroy manicures fast. Users want real longevity advice, not just pretty pictures.
4. **"I can't find designs that work for both work and the beach"** — Versatility is a genuine need: users want one mani that carries across professional settings and summer activities.
5. **"I want to look trendy but not high-maintenance"** — Short nail users often choose short for practicality; they don't want designs that require constant upkeep or complex salon visits.

### User Sentiment
Aspirational but mildly frustrated — they know short nails are having a moment but struggle to find curated, practical guidance rather than endless unedited galleries.

